<br>
Our main concern is personality.  Not only what kind of person you are in game, but how you come across, your interests, and your maturity.<br>
<br>
Our second concern is your ability to play your class.  We have little to no interest in teaching people the basics of their class.  It's not a problem if you haven't raided before, but you better know what you're doing in a group and have decent knowledge of the game world.<br>
<br>
Our third concern is when you're generally online.  We are a guild based in Eastern Standard Time.<br>
<br>
Finally, we are somewhat interested in your gear, flags, level, and keys, though this is less important than the above.  We strongly prefer if you have an Enduring Breath item and Valor flag, though lacking these items/flags will certainly not keep us from inviting great people.<br>
<br>
We will not generally accept applicants under level 60 except when the applicant is a really special person.  Even then, we will not consider you if you're below level 50 even if you are Jesus Christ  49 Cleric.  Those under level 60 will be considered Secondary characters when it comes to loot distribution even if they are Primaries.<br>
<br>
UPDATE: Applications will be moved to the private sections of the board to preserve the applicant's privacy.  If you have questions about your application, contact one of us in game.<br>
<br>
Some suggestions on things to talk about in your application in addition to the above: Why don't you tell us what you find fun in EQ? What bothers you? What the biggest raid you were ever on was like. What your goals are. What guild(s) you've been a part of and what you like/didn't like about them. What's your favorite group make-up? What do you hope to find in Zero Sum?<br>
<br>
